Angola has become a member of the International Monetary Fund and the World Bank and its affiliates. 

World Bank officials said Angola signed agreements making it a member of the bank, the International Development Association, the International Finance Corp. and the Multilateral Investment Guarantee Agency. 

Separately, Angola's finance minister, Augusto Teixeira de Matos, signed his country's membership agreement with the 

Both the IMF and the World Bank now have 152 member countries. 

Angola, a West African country, will be eligible for economic development credits from the IDA, a World Bank affiliate that provides loans to poor developing nations. 

